main event: An unidentified object was spotted by two observers viewing the stars through a telescope in Tinley Park, Illinois on August 4, 1965.
interesting points: The object moved at a lightning speed, about 2-3 degrees per second, and then turned and went north.
One observer said the object turned 90 degrees and went out of sight, while the other said it turned only 10 degrees.
The object appeared as a star-like object and only lasted about 16-17 seconds.
Possible explanations considered include an airplane turning on its landing lights, a meteor, or a satellite, but the report concludes the sighting is unidentified.
The case was forwarded to Project Blue Book for further investigation.
witnesses: two observers viewing the stars through a telescope
